DataElementConcept.preferredDefinition: Information pertaining to the determination of oxygen-hemoglobin saturation of blood either by withdrawing a sample and passing it through a classical photoelectric oximeter or by electrodes attached to some translucent part of the body like finger, earlobe, or skin fold with a percentage level.

ObjectClass.preferredDefinition:
The determination of oxygen-hemoglobin saturation of blood either by withdrawing a sample and passing
it through a classical photoelectric oximeter or by electrodes attached to some translucent part of the body like finger,
earlobe, or skin fold. It includes non-invasive oxygen monitoring by pulse oximetry.

Concepts.definition: The measurement of the ratio of oxygenated hemoglobin to total hemoglobin in the blood.
